gomodel:SYNGO_4681  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: Puncta for RAMP1 colocalize with puncta for VGLUT2 and Synaptophysin in the dorsal horn of the rat spinal cord (fig 5). Some of the puncta also colocalize with enkephalins, an opioid marker.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Immunohistochemistry\nAdult male Sprague-Dawley rats (250 -300 g, Harlan, Indianapolis, IN, USA) were killed with pentobarbital (100 mg/kg) and fixed immediately by aortic perfusion of 100 ml phosphate buffer [...]\n\nAntibodies\nRAMP1 rabbit serum CURE9892 Raised against the C-terminal 9 residues of human RAMP1" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4681" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

